---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import AmazonButton from '../../components/AmazonButton.astro';

const stones = [
  {
    asin: "B07T8D2W8M",
    name: "Harvia Olivine Sauna Rocks",
    price: "~$45",
    tag: "BEST OVERALL",
    tagColor: "bg-amber-100 text-amber-800",
    summary: "Olivine is the gold standard for sauna stones. High density, excellent heat retention, and it doesn't crack or deteriorate quickly like cheaper rocks. Harvia sources these properly — round, smooth, and sized correctly for most home heaters.",
    weight: "22 lbs",
    type: "Olivine",
    compatible: "Most 6-9 kW heaters"
  },
  {
    asin: "B07T8JVK3W",
    name: "Harvia Granite Sauna Stones",
    price: "~$38",
    tag: "BUDGET PICK",
    tagColor: "bg-green-100 text-green-800",
    summary: "Solid granite stones at a lower price than olivine. Granite holds heat well and is widely available. It deteriorates faster than olivine over time but is a perfectly good choice for most home users who replace stones every 3-5 years anyway.",
    weight: "22 lbs",
    type: "Granite",
    compatible: "Universal"
  }
];
---
<Base
  title="Best Sauna Stones (2025) — What Rocks to Use and When to Replace Them"
  description="The best sauna stones for electric and wood-burning heaters. What rocks to use, how many you need, and when to replace them."
  canonical="/guides/best-sauna-stones"
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-700 font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Accessories</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-stone-900 leading-tight mb-4">
        Best Sauna Stones (2025): What Rocks to Use and When to Replace
      </h1>
      <p class="text-stone-500 text-sm">Updated January 2025 · 7 min read</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mt-4">
        Most sauna heaters come with a basic set of rocks. They work fine initially. But after a year or two of regular use, cheap stones crack, deteriorate, and produce less steam. Here's what actually matters when buying sauna stones.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8">
      <h2 class="font-bold text-stone-800 mb-3">Stone Types at a Glance</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        {[
          ["Olivine (peridot)", "Best heat retention, longest lifespan, premium choice", "★★★★★"],
          ["Granite", "Good heat retention, widely available, budget-friendly", "★★★★"],
          ["Vulcanite (basalt/lava)", "Excellent heat retention, good for large heaters", "★★★★"],
          ["Soapstone", "Very smooth steam, used in custom builds, harder to find", "★★★★"],
          ["Random field stones", "Never use — uneven mineral content causes cracking and potential explosions", "✗"],
        ].map(([type, desc, rating]) => (
          <div class="flex gap-3 bg-white rounded-lg px-4 py-2">
            <span class="font-semibold text-stone-800 w-36 shrink-0">{type}</span>
            <span class="text-stone-600 flex-1">{desc}</span>
            <span class="text-amber-600 shrink-0">{rating}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-5 mb-8">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-red-800 mb-2">Important Safety Note</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Never use rocks you picked up outside in your sauna heater. Random stones may contain trapped moisture or minerals that expand violently when heated. This can cause the rocks to explode. Only use sauna-specific stones sold for this purpose.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-6 text-stone-900">Top Picks</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-10">
      {stones.map(stone => (
        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <div class="bg-stone-50 border-b border-stone-200 px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900">{stone.name}</h3>
            <span class={`text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full ${stone.tagColor}`}>{stone.tag}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <div class="flex gap-6 mb-3 text-sm text-stone-500">
              <span>Type: <strong class="text-stone-700">{stone.type}</strong></span>
              <span>Weight: <strong class="text-stone-700">{stone.weight}</strong></span>
              <span>Fits: <strong class="text-stone-700">{stone.compatible}</strong></span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mb-4">{stone.summary}</p>
            <AmazonButton asin={stone.asin} price={stone.price} />
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-stone-900">How to Use Sauna Stones Correctly</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">

      <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">How Many Stones Do You Need?</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Your heater manual specifies the stone capacity. Most 6 kW heaters hold 20-35 lbs of stones. More stone mass means better heat retention and more satisfying löyly. Don't underfill the heater — it reduces steam quality significantly.</p>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm">
          {[
            ["3-4 kW heater", "10-15 lbs"],
            ["6 kW heater", "20-25 lbs"],
            ["8-9 kW heater", "30-40 lbs"],
            ["12+ kW heater", "50-80 lbs"],
          ].map(([size, weight]) => (
            <div class="flex justify-between border-b border-stone-100 pb-1">
              <span class="text-stone-600">{size}</span>
              <span class="font-semibold text-stone-800">{weight}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">How to Load the Stones</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Stack larger stones on the bottom around the heating elements. Smaller stones fill gaps on top. Leave some space between stones for air circulation — tightly packed stones restrict airflow and can overheat the elements. Most manufacturers include a loading diagram.</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mt-3">Run the heater empty for the first hour to burn off any residue from new stones before your first session.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">When to Replace Sauna Stones</h3>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm">Sauna stones degrade over time. The heat cycling causes micro-fractures that eventually cause the stones to crumble. Signs you need new stones:</p>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-sm text-stone-600">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-amber-600">•</span>Stones are visibly crumbling or cracked</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-amber-600">•</span>Steam production has decreased noticeably</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-amber-600">•</span>You hear hissing or popping sounds during normal use</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-amber-600">•</span>It's been 3-5 years of regular use</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-stone-600 text-sm mt-3">Replace all stones at once rather than mixing old and new — they have different thermal properties and mixed loads produce uneven heat.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-6">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-stone-900 mb-3">More sauna guides</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li><a href="/guides/best-electric-sauna-heaters" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline font-medium">Best Electric Sauna Heaters</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/best-wood-burning-sauna-heaters" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline font-medium">Best Wood-Burning Sauna Heaters</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/sauna-maintenance-guide" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline font-medium">Sauna Maintenance Guide</a></li>
        <li><a href="/guides/how-to-use-a-sauna" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline font-medium">How to Use a Sauna (Beginner Guide)</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </article>
</Base>
